# `picker.recent` (Ctrl+R) — fuzzy picker over most-recently-opened files,
# newest first. Open three files, then verify the picker shows them in
# reverse-open order.

write a.txt "alpha"
write b.txt "beta"
write c.txt "gamma"

open a.txt
open b.txt
open c.txt

# Switch back to a.txt so c.txt is the alternate buffer (not the active).
open a.txt

command picker.recent

# The picker title says "Recent files". All three filenames should appear.
expect screen contains "Recent"
expect screen contains "a.txt"
expect screen contains "b.txt"
expect screen contains "c.txt"

# Accept the highlighted (top) row.
key enter
# Whichever file was on top — most-recently-non-active — is now active.
# We can't easily test which; just confirm we exited the picker.
expect screen lacks "Recent files"
